# Rust build output
/target
**/target

# The polkadot-sdk monorepo clone used for the M0 de-risk build (huge, re-cloneable
# at tag polkadot-stable2603-3 / commit e3737178ec726cffe506c907263aaaa417893fd0).
/_sdk

# Node deps (acceptance script / future app + indexer)
node_modules/
# The anchor-relayer reuses the app's deps via a node_modules SYMLINK (not a dir, so the
# pattern above misses it). Recreate locally: ln -sfn ../../app/node_modules node_modules
services/anchor-relayer/node_modules
# The M6 committee tooling does the same (symlink to the indexer's deps).
# Recreate locally: ln -sfn ../indexer/node_modules services/committee/node_modules
services/committee/node_modules
# The D1 sponsored-bind relay also reuses the app's deps via a symlink.
# Recreate locally: ln -sfn ../../app/node_modules services/sponsored-bind-relay/node_modules
services/sponsored-bind-relay/node_modules

# Secrets / local env (never commit real creds). The committed manifests are the
# *.env.example files (root + services/indexer); the live .env / .env*.local files stay local.
.env
**/.env
.env*.local
**/.env*.local
!.env.example
!**/.env.example

# Editor / OS cruft
*.rs.bk
.DS_Store

# Local chain state (we use --tmp/--dev for M0)
/state
*.log

# Operator-keyed network output from scripts/gen-chainspec.mjs — contains keys.json (secret
# mnemonics) + env.sh + the generated chain spec. NEVER commit. (Override the dir with OUT=.)
/network
**/keys.json

# Stateful secrets the services write into the data dir (relayer wallet SEED + the anchor cursor) and a
# filled-in systemd EnvironmentFile (signing seeds + DB_PASS). Defaults live OUTSIDE the repo, but
# OWNER_FILE/COGNO_DATA_DIR/STATE_FILE can point inside a checkout — this is the backstop. NOTE: no bare
# **/vault.json here — vault.json is a committed build artifact (app/src/lib/cardano/, contracts/).
**/owner.json
**/anchor-state.json
cogno.env
**/cogno.env
!**/cogno.env.example
